article.headline: Fordham 66, Manhattan 57
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Brenton Butler and Chris Bethel both scored 15 points and Fordham beat Manhattan 66-57 on Wednesday night in the 100th meeting of the schools located in the Bronx. Sebastian Greene added 11 points and seven rebounds for the visiting Rams (3-3). Devon Austin scored 13 points and Rashad Green had 10 for the Jaspers (3-3). The first meeting was in 1911-12. Manhattan holds a 51-49 lead in the series. Bethel had all of his 15 points, plus five rebounds, in the first half as Fordham took a 36-29 lead. Darryl Crawford scored to cap a 9-0 Manhattan run that cut the Rams' lead to 39-38 with 13:41 left in the game. Butler's basket with 8:03 to go increased Fordham's lead to 55-44. Jamel Ferguson scored with 4:45 left to narrow the lead to 55-53 but the Jaspers came no closer.
